choices.text:
the transition of skills. We covered so much in the short amount of time that kids didnt have enough time to process maturity on many levels.

Hmachshevet Yeladeemi II students start to learn learning excellence skills at the end of their 3rd year. After students quote are quoting in on some of the ways of learning they have to try to learn something on their own as a freshman. That is the last thing they need, so much stress.

I know the YMCA is looking at new ways to teach old topics. Starting earlier has been suggested and while I havent read too far into it, starting earlier would suggest getting even better and more skills earlier and making the transition that much more easy.

the YMCA for even thinking of this as a solution is commendable, Does the maker of the program think that graduates dont need transition programs in college?

From my experience, core skills should be learned in high school but there is definitely room for electives and advanced studies.

I’m not a fan of blanket statements about mixing day and boarding settings and at my son’s “Olim Brit” school, they are working very hard to balance attitudes and prepare their 7th graders by dedicating a day (several times a year) early on to teach skills for balancing life.
